Network Security Groups (NSGs) are used to filter network traffic in Azure VNets using security rules.

They allow or deny traffic based on:

* Source and destination IP
* Port numbers
* Protocols

For example, an NSG can allow HTTP (port 80) traffic but block all other ports.

A real-life use case is securing backend servers so they are only accessible from frontend servers.

Another example is restricting SSH/RDP access to specific IP addresses for security.

NSGs provide fine-grained control over network security.
